{
  "texts": [
    "In this case, the main peak is shifted to w < 1, driven by the overpopulated wings of the smeared M µµ distribution.",
    "A secondary peak/shoulder appears around w ∼ 1.5, corresponding to the underpopulated M µµ resonance.",
    "It is interesting to compare this weight distributions from the smeared M µµ resonance and the smeared distortion of the JetNet data in Fig. 2.",
    "Although both are driven by a smearing, the weight distributions are very different.",
    "For the smeared jets the maximum of the weight distribution appears at w > 1, representing the actual peak configurations, while for the LHC events the maximum of the weight distribution is shifted to w < 1, driven by the shoulders of the smeared peak."
  ]
}